      • complete

        public boolean complete​(InsertionSource insertSource)
        Description copied from class: AbstractComponent
        This method uses an InsertionSource object to completely control the insertion of this component. A valid implementation of this method must handle adding the component to the target model, initializing the component, and adding an appropriate undo-able edit to the source's CompoundEdit.

        When this method is called, this component has not been added to the model available from InsertionSource.getModel(). Refer to the source code documentation for InsertionSource for more information on this process.

        Note: Components that implement this method should not implement AbstractComponent.complete() as it will not be called if this method returns true.

        Overrides:
        complete in class AbstractComponent
        Parameters:
        insertSource - the InsertionSource that should be used to guide the component insertion process.
        Returns:
        true if this component supports component initialization via an InsertionSource object; false otherwise.
        See Also:
        InsertionSource.componentAdded(AbstractComponent, boolean), InsertionSource.getEdit(), InsertionSource.getModel()

      • reconnectIdentReferences

        public void reconnectIdentReferences​(boolean preserveUnresolved,
                                     boolean useDbId)
        Description copied from class: GenericObject
        Resets this component's internal ident references to refer to appropriate components in the current AbstractModel. Intended for use after adding a component to a model and thus it's DB_ID will have been set to it's ident in the previous model. For ident references use find__ByDbId to find the new component, then store it's ident.

        Note: If this component's DB_ID is 0 this method does nothing.

        Specified by:
        reconnectIdentReferences in interface IdentHolder
        Overrides:
        reconnectIdentReferences in class AbstractComponent
        Parameters:
        preserveUnresolved - if true, ident references that aren't resolvable will be left dangling, if false, they will be set to 0.
        useDbId - if true, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByDB_ID; if false, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByIdent
